rComments: keep up with this class. complete his entire recommended study plans that he posts super useful, do the hw again and again, and do extra practice questions online if you want a great mark overall a good prof who explains things well.

Prof Conheady wasn't a bad prof, but expects that all students spend at least 40 hours per week for class related things (10hrs for his), not realizing that people have jobs, families and other classes. Lots of homework and reading material. Realistically, if you attend all classes, spend time studying and taking thorough notes, it's an easy pass.

Be prepared to read and practice hardcore in order to do well. Conheady's teaching method seems so backwards; why are we doing the reading by ourselves and then doing the practice questions in class? I would take another prof if possible.

By far the worst professor I've ever had in my entire life. He DOES NOT care about the students, and actually tries to mess our grades up as much as possible. He'll say that something isn't covered on a midterm, will then put that material on the midterm, and then give us a measly 1 mark even though the question was worth 12 marks. AVOID!!!!!!!!!!!

Weekly quizzes on the upcoming week's subject and tells you to study 9 hours for them, then throws in questions on those quizzes that are actually two weeks ahead so you aren't ready to answer them. Prof thinks students only have his class, because the workload is unbearable. Get ready to do all three midterms on the weekend and not in class time.

Absolutely terrible. Classes were scheduled twice a week, yet completely online. He uploads study sequences with textbook readings, Wiley plus videos, and videos he uploads which you clearly see from his computer screen are from 2013 and 2014. Exams are fair but you will spend ridiculous amounts of time on readings and his videos. Absolutely avoid

This prof shows that the accounting education at Telfer is stale and full of itself. The classes are completely useless as he expects you to be a CPA accountant the moment you join the class, which is absurd. Telfer really needs to infuse its accounting department with some new blood, because this prof is only here to let you feel bad and useless.

Despite passing intermediate accounting with a B, I couldnt remember a single bit of what Ive learnt because prof Conheady never actually taught you anything and you had to learn by rote to pass exams. What is the point of going to school if we neither get high grades nor knowledge? I now understand how Louis XIV felt when he got guillotiné.

conheady should not be teaching. Midterms were unnecessarily difficult, and his teaching style is very old fashioned. Pretty much read the textbook myself and completed the practice question and never attended class. Regret taking this prof!! AVOID

This professor is one of the worst professors in the entire school. Never taught in class, posts 3-4 hour worth of lectures a week. never teaches anything expects you to learn the stuff on your own. The only way to pass is to study the book and solve the questions. Absolute garbage of a professor.

I highly doubt that Telfer opens the accounting program to troll us. The accounting department feels like that it is monopolised by a few people, and Prof Conheady is one of them. This prof follows the teaching ideology in the early 1960s, which is to teach nothing and wait for certain students to pass the class through natural selection. Horrible.

At final exam, he announced that international students can apply access to exam in another time. I left Ottawa after the application deadline, and emailed him few days before exam to ask if I can get the access, then he disappeared, for 4 days, he should at least inform me about this so that I can allocate my time having two exams from 2am to 9am.

This prof should just choose retirement since he is too old to fit into the modern accounting system. His teaching methods are outdated since he will throw all the work to you and expect you to teach yourself everything. Even if you get an A+ in his class, there is nothing to be proud of because the knowledge only applies in the 1940s.

Terrible prof; switched everything to Mcgraw Hill Connect so had to purchase the online textbook again and all the exams and tests/assignments are over that platform. Lectures are boring and he talks himself into confusion; better off just reading the text and attending class to do the weekly quizzes and assignments. Final and midterms were easy.

Conheady is by far one of the worst professors I have encountered in my undergrad career. The workload that this prof assigns to their students is equivalent to 2-3 courses worth. Midterm exams were unnecessarily difficult. Don't expect to get higher than a C+. Prepare to self study and waster your tuition money. Avoid this prof at all cost!

Refused to reveal how many questions were on the final exam which contained questions on separate pages with no ability to go back. Students could not check how many questions there were total and had to write blindly. Second midterm began 10 minutes late, and there was already insufficient time per calculation. Three deliverables per week.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Test heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I had Prof. Conheady for Inter 1 and 2. Make this classes much easier by reading the chapter and doing problems before class not after. This class is hard because of the amount of content to learn in a small time frame, but Conheady is very clear about what he will test on and really does want everyone to do well

Attending his lectures will be useless if you haven't read the chapters ahead of time. Stopped going to his lectures at some point and taught myself from the textbook. To pass: read the textbook in detail, ATTEND DGDs and PRACTICE (like crazy). Tip: he rarely posts slides but the WileyPlus textbook had online slides that were super helpful

Otherwise, I suggest that you change your major for good.

This prof doesn't teach at all! He simply just throws everything at you and expects you to learn everything yourself. I cannot imagine how those people get B or A with him as the prof. rComments: Absolutely terrible prof who doesn't teach at all.

Honestly I have taken Intermediate Acc. 1 in Algonquin and I thought she was bad, but compare to prof. Conheady, she is a 1-2 while prof Conheady is a 10 (10 being the worst). He literally doesn't teach you a single thing, but rather waste your time by pulling financial reports of a company and commenting about it. RUN FROM HIM or FAIL

Conheady's lectures are insightful into the applications of accounting in real life. The lectures themselves are focused heavily on walking through the solutions to the homework problems and oftentimes offer little guidance on how to solve the problems. To pass you must dedicate a lot of time to doing HW questions before class.

Conheady was clearly passionate about the subject and was interesting to listen to. However, the exams were unfairly hard. On top of that, lots of points are taken off for small mistakes. Get ready to study, but even the textbook and practice exam problems don't compare to the exam. I nearly switched out of accounting because of him and this class
Read the textbook and go to DGDs. Conheady's lectures are not useful for the tests. Just practice past exams and DGD problems
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: The key to this class isn't going to lectures, it's reading the textbook right through, getting all the practise you can, going to DGDs, and ASKING QUESTIONS! Conheady will clearly answer any question you have. But if you don't work hard you'll probably fail. Exams are fair, prof is good (lectures boring), insane volume of content to learn though.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Prof. Conheady cares about his students and replies emails quickly. You just need to work very very very hard to do well on the exams. Midterm 1 was fair and the problems were similar to the past exams he posted. Midterm 2 and the Final were difficult. But if you do all his practice questions over and over again, you are guaranteed to pass.

Tips to succeed with Conheady: Attend all DGDs - problems are from past exams & much tougher than current exams. Practice w/ ALL his resources (eg Bondbeagle) as exam problems draw from them & they're way more difficult than homework problems. Past exams are critical. Use BAII Plus for speed. It's possible to do well, but you have to work hard!

rComments: The workload is a lot so i recommend doing the practice problems and keeping up to date on the lectures in order to have a good grade. rComments: You pretty much need to teach your self in this class. The DGDs are much more useful than his classes. Hands down one of the worst profs in Telfer, avoid at all costs.

Brian is very knowledgeable in accounting, but not very much so in teaching abilities. It's not that he doesn't know what things mean, it's just that his idea of teaching is by showing the final results rather than by explanation. Heavily recommend utilizing the textbook for explanations and definitions. Old midterms and exams were golden.

His method of teaching is backwards. Usually, a prof teaches the material and then students do practice questions on their own time. With Conheady, he goes through exercises in class and expects you to magically know how to do them. You are expected to learn all of the material yourself. (and there is a lot to know)
His method of teaching is absolutely useless. I finished with a good grade, but no thanks to him

Conheady is a terible proffessor. He doesn't teach you the material covered in class, just simply does the assigned questions from the textbook and expects you to know how to do it already. Then when comes the midterm or final, he puts questions you have never seen in the asigned homework on to exam expecting you to know exactly how to do it.

Brian is a nice guy and means well. However, the way he approaches lectures is not the greatest. I would much rather him cover the chapter's material briefly before diving right into questions. He assigns 20 questions per chapter that he expects you to know when it comes time for an exam...

While I do understand Intermediate Accounting 1 and 2 are hard classes regardless of  where and who you take them with, Brian just makes it worse. Useless lectures unrelated to material on exams, just blabbers on about cricket and Australian Christmas trees. Very unprofessional and condescending.

To do well in this course you must focus on the most important materials taught in class. Brian Conheady tends to focus on the main questions in class that would most likely be tested on exams.  This course is tough not because of the professor but because of the sheer volume of material that needs to be learnt in a short period of time.

Intermediate Accounting is an intriguing course overall; however, Brian seems to be under the impression that his dry lectures cover even a portion of his exams, specifically the final exam. Regardless of his research, there needs to be an addition to the accounting lectures here at the Telfer School of Managment.
Needs improvement

Worst professor I've had in my 3 years at uOttawa, hands down. Professor Conheady is a nice guy who does care about his students and wants us to reach our potential. He makes it so that you have to teach yourself everything and the course is designed for your failure. rComments: Best prof if you're taking Inter 1 or Inter 2. No matter what prof you get you're going to have to read the material yourself since there's so much content in each chapter. He structures his lectures really well and focuses on problems that will most likely be on the midterm/final. He also has online recordings where he goes through problems.

He is super helpful and care for students (even after we passed the course, he still emailed all of us about CPA/ other career related issues). The way he teaches this course: participation and attendance MATTERS! you need to be prepared by reading cases every week. The midterm and final is taken from the cases done in class. Easy.

Conheady does a good job of teaching you how to approach SPECIFIC questions. Although he does not teach the material during the lectures, if you're a person that can learn from a textbook then you can manage the heavy workload of Intermediate 1 and 2. The exams are difficult, but they are manageable if you put in the time and effort - 9 hrs/ week
Expects you to do the reading/learn the chapters before-hand and as a result, doesn't really teach the course.
you have to eat the book and learn everything on your own. teaches mostly exercises. so do every problems multiple times. tests are also confusing, long and hard
Really care about students. Open for feedback, generous office hour.  However exam is super hard, no bell curve, nothing. You earn what you put into it.
If you go to lecture and do the assigned questions, you should  be ok.  He is helpful.
Go to class and participate.

Excellent professor!! Easy to understand and follow the class if, and only if, you read the material before class. The assessments are challenging. This is the first of two "make or break" classes for accounting, but with Conheady you are in good hands!!

I failed Inter 1 with him the first time, and actually managed a decent grade in Inter 2. After (re) taking Inter 1 with Collier in the summer I was terrified, but his teaching has surprisingly gotten better. The last 5 classes he actually worked through examples with the class. Super nice guy and teaching getting better slowly.

Professor Conheady, is a very intelligent and nice man. Otherwise, he is a terrible professor. Please avoid if you plan on doing well and continuing your studies in accounting. Very confusing, does not explain concepts. You literally have to learn the course material by your self. Put in the 9+ hours of outside work recommended!

He is the worst prof at Ottawa u. Boring, doesn't stick to the point, doesn't use his own slides, extremely confusing and doesn't mark fairly at all. Stay away or wait you can't because he's the only one who teaches this course.

Great prof. I highly recommend reading the slides or the chapter in advance, because he covers the finer, more important details in class. That way you will have a greater understanding of the material! Professor Conheady is highly knowledgeable about accounting, so if you have any questions about accounting as a career, definitely talk to him.

The worst prof at Telfer hands down. Lectures are a waste of time as he just goes through problem solutions and slides that aren't even his. This class sucked.

Worst professor ever. I would highly recommend you take the summer courses to avoid him at all costs. His expectations of students are far to high. Marks go out the door. Midterm was not fair at all. Half of the students dropped out of his course. The average for the class was really low.

Great Professor. Really knows his material, and is able to explain it effectively. Expectations are made clear, and exams are a mirror image of what was covered in class. Conheady is not a good accounting prof. He rarely conveys the subject matter effectively. The midterm in this class was fair and straight forward but the final exam was unfair and really hard. Absolutely terrible professor. Avoid at ALL cost. If collier is teaching the same course, please switch sections immediately upon reading this. Terrible. If you're stuck with him, kiss your grade goodbye. He is easily the absolute worst professor I've ever had in both college and university. Man o man. Collier is a much better accounting prof. Conheady talks and talks about nothing and will never finished an example. The most useless teacher I have ever had. Don't go to his lecture or even ask him anything because he will misinform you and go on very long tangents. Just skip his classes and focus on the textbook instead, it will give you way better results.

Had him for managerial and intermediate acct 2.  Very knowledgeable, smart prof., knows what he's talking about.  Nice guy, however, he lacks teaching/communication skills. The most part I can not bear about this professor is unfairness in marking. He assign you a mark at his will and never have supportive information to show why you get that mark. He always say one sentence that "you should do more than what you did".This feedback is useless and unhelpful at all

Entirely case-based discussions.You do learn interesting aspects of management.However the course is open ended to a fault and don't think most student really "got" it.Most us did get tidbits of understanding,but at the end I think many of us were left confused and vague about cases.High expectation for preparation and attendance is mandatory.

Very demanding prof. Expects you have read before coming to class. This class involves alot of studying and hard work.  I found the useless as he only focused on the assigned homework.  He didn't do much teaching of the material.  He tends to go off topic in class.

This is a demanding class and the prof is not that helpful. His classes are mostly exercises from the book. He assumes that you know the material before coming to class. He knows a lot of stuff but he can be a little bit monotonous. Between Larochelle and him, take him! He's australian by the way.
